# Campaign Engine — Pairing Session Recap
*March 2026 — Gitz vs Slaves Path to Glory Campaign*

---

## What We Built

Over the course of this campaign we've built a **multi-agent narrative campaign engine** for running a Warhammer Age of Sigmar Path to Glory campaign. It isn't just a rules tracker — it's a story machine that manages three intertwined systems: **army state**, **narrative lore**, and **battle design**, with each informing the other.

### The Agents

| Agent | File | Role |
|---|---|---|
| **Campaign Engine** | `Path to Glory - Campaign Gem Instructions.md` | Generates battleplans, objectives, asymmetric VP, underdog mechanics |
| **Aftermath Engine** | `Path to Glory - Aftermath Gem Instructions.md` | Processes battle reports, manages rank-ups/scars, runs Arc Compass survey |
| **Arc Planner** | `AI Planning/arc-planning.md` | Living reference for narrative arcs, active threads, character development seeds |

### The Documents

| Document | Role |
|---|---|
| `Campaign Lore/Battle Bible.md` | **Source of truth** — army rosters, GP, wounds, rank-ups, scars |
| `Campaign Lore/battle-summary.md` | Battle-by-battle reference — hooks, results, battlefield design, tracker tables |
| `Campaign Lore/campaign-novel.md` | Living prose novel — character development, dialogue, location intros |
| `AI Planning/arc-planning.md` | Arc themes, character seeds, Arc Compass response log |
| `WH P2G/Path to Glory.md` | Core rules reference |

